<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2">
  <Document>
    <name>Kerala - River Basin Impact Info</name>
    <description>Detailed information on the impact of flooding on major river basins.</description>
    
    <Style id="basinBalloon">
      <BalloonStyle>
        <text><![CDATA[
          <h3>$[name]</h3>
          <p><b>Status:</b> $[status]</p>
          <p><b>Impact:</b> $[description]</p>
          <p><b>Key Reservoir:</b> $[reservoir]</p>
        ]]></text>
        <bgColor>ffffffff</bgColor>
      </BalloonStyle>
      <PolyStyle>
         <color>5500ffff</color> <!-- Light Yellow/Gold transparency -->
         <outcome>0</outcome>
      </PolyStyle>
    </Style>

    <Folder>
      <name>River Basins</name>
      
      <Placemark>
        <name>Periyar River Basin</name>
        <styleUrl>#basinBalloon</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="status"><value>Critical Overflow</value></Data>
          <Data name="reservoir"><value>Idukki Arch Dam, Idamalayar</value></Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <description>The opening of all 5 shutters of the Idukki dam for the first time in 26 years released 700,000 liters/sec, devastating downstream areas including Aluva and Kochi airport.</description>
        <Polygon>
          <tessellate>1</tessellate>
          <outerBoundaryIs>
            <LinearRing>
              <coordinates>
                77.00,9.80,0
                76.80,10.10,0
                76.25,10.05,0
                76.25,9.90,0
                76.50,9.70,0
                77.00,9.80,0
              </coordinates>
            </LinearRing>
          </outerBoundaryIs>
        </Polygon>
      </Placemark>

      <Placemark>
        <name>Pamba River Basin</name>
        <styleUrl>#basinBalloon</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="status"><value>Severe Inundation</value></Data>
          <Data name="reservoir"><value>Kakki, Anathode</value></Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <description>Intense rainfall in the catchment areas led to the opening of Kakki and Anathode dams, flooding Ranni, Aranmula, and Chengannur.</description>
        <Polygon>
          <tessellate>1</tessellate>
          <outerBoundaryIs>
            <LinearRing>
              <coordinates>
                77.15,9.35,0
                76.80,9.40,0
                76.50,9.30,0
                76.60,9.20,0
                77.15,9.35,0
              </coordinates>
            </LinearRing>
          </outerBoundaryIs>
        </Polygon>
      </Placemark>

      <Placemark>
        <name>Chalakudy River Basin</name>
        <styleUrl>#basinBalloon</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="status"><value>Flash Floods</value></Data>
          <Data name="reservoir"><value>Parambikulam (upstream)</value></Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <description>Faced unprecedented rising water levels due to heavy inflows from Parambikulam and Sholayar, submerging Chalakudy town.</description>
        <Polygon>
          <tessellate>1</tessellate>
          <outerBoundaryIs>
            <LinearRing>
              <coordinates>
                76.80,10.35,0
                76.50,10.35,0
                76.30,10.20,0
                76.60,10.15,0
                76.80,10.35,0
              </coordinates>
            </LinearRing>
          </outerBoundaryIs>
        </Polygon>
      </Placemark>

    </Folder>
  </Document>
</kml>
